description:
For an international project in Chennai, we are urgently looking for a Senior PeopleSoft Developer to assist with the implementation of a Work Force Planning system. Candidates need to have at least 5 years of PeopleSoft experience.










 Candidates need to be willing to work in Chennai!










 We are looking for a motivated contractor. This position is long\\-term. Candidates need to be fluent in English.










**Tasks and responsibilities:** 



* Develop, test and deliver a process to pull staff demographic data (e.g., grade, title, department), Position data from PeopleSoft;
* Develop, test, and deliver a process to load historical data from a SQL Server database to PeopleSoft;
* Produce completed and well tested programs which meet user satisfaction and acceptance and precisely reflect the requirements from technical specs;
* Take functional specs and develop high quality technical specs from functional specs;
* Enable workflow in certain areas of the system;
* Adhere to project schedules and report progress regularly;
* Prepare technical documents like technical specs, flow diagrams, ER diagrams, user manuals etc;
* Prepare CMM required documentation for project, when applicable (Impact Analysis and Design, Test Cases, SMR);
* Ensure that Bank policies, procedures and standards are factored into project design and development;
* Conduct Peer Review on Code and Test Cases prepared by other team members, to assess quality and compliance with coding standards;
* Prepare weekly status reports and participate in status meetings \\- highlighting issues and constraints that would impact timely delivery of work program items;
* Communicate proactively with other team members and team lead. Participate in the estimation of work plans, test plans and implementation plans;









 Profile:



* Bachelor or Master degree;
* \\+8 years of IT experience;
* \\+5 years relevant experience in building PeopleSoft systems using PeopleSoft and Database technologies, preferably work experience in Peoplesoft 9\\.2
* Excellent knowledge of PeopleTools, Peoplesoft Application Designer, Peoplecode, SQR and overall excellent technical skills on the Peoplesoft Development platform;
* Expertise in SQL, PL/SQL and Oracle platform;
* Expertise in SQR programming for producing complex reports and batch processes;
* Expertise with Peoplesoft Mobile / Fluid technologies;
* Peoplesoft Workflow knowledge expected and working knowledge would be desirable;
* Sufficient knowledge and working experience with rule based systems;
* Knowledge of Peoplesoft HR table infrastructure;
* Proven and demonstrated experience in full system development life cycle – Analysis, Design, Programming, Testing, Implementation, and Maintenance;
* Sound understanding of and implementation experience with issue tracking, and source code repository;
* Fluent in English;
